text: Korneyevka () is a rural locality (a village) and the administrative center of Korneyevsky Selsoviet, Meleuzovsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 1,018 as of 2010. There are 11 streets. == Geography == It is located 46 km from Meleuz. == References == Category:Rural localities in Meleuzovsky District
title: Korneyevka
